.documentation
  %section.intro
    =image_tag "/images/ps3.jpg", class: "display"
    %p
      Allows user to interact with Cylon.js devices using a PS3 game controller.

  %section.how-to
    %h2 How to establish a connection and setup the driver
    :markdown
          :::javascript
          require 'Cylon.js'
          connection :joystick, :adaptor => :joystick
          device :controller, :driver => :ps3, :connection => :joystick, :interval => 0.1

  %section.public-events
    %h2 Events
    %dl.methods 
      %dt button_left_joystiq
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if a left joystick click event occured.
      %dt button_right_joystiq
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if a right joystick click event occured.
      %dt button_square
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the square button was pressed.
      %dt button_x
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the 'x' button was pressed.
      %dt button_circle
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the circle button was pressed.
      %dt button_triangle
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the triangle button was pressed.
      %dt button_l1
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the l1 button was pressed.
      %dt button_l2
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the l2 button was pressed.
      %dt button_r1
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the r1 button was pressed.
      %dt button_r2
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the r2 button was pressed.
      %dt button_start
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the start button was pressed.
      %dt button_select
      %dd  Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the select button was pressed.
      %dt button_home
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if the home button was pressed.
      %dt joystick
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if a joystick event occured, you can access values x, y, s(joystick number, 0 and 1 for left and right).
      %dt joystick_0
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if a joystick_0 event occured, you can access values x, y.
      %dt joystick_1
      %dd Get's triggered every interval amount of time if a joystick_1 event occured, you can access values x, y.


